Here's the PlantUML component diagram focusing on control flow for the arkaneshiro_Sound-Zone application:

```plantuml
@startuml arkaneshiro_Sound-Zone

package "Frontend" {
    [App] as App
    [Home] as Home
    [Profile] as Profile
    [Dashboard] as Dashboard
    [SoundDetail] as SoundDetail
    [Sound] as Sound
    [SoundBar] as SoundBar
    [Upload] as Upload
    [LoginForm] as LoginForm
    [RegistrationForm] as RegistrationForm
    [NavBar] as NavBar
    
    package "Redux" {
        [Actions] as ReduxActions
        [Reducers] as ReduxReducers
        [Store] as ReduxStore
    }
}

package "Backend" {
    [Node.js/Express] as Backend
    [PostgreSQL] as Database
    [Cloudinary] as Cloudinary
}

' Control Flow Relationships
App --> Home : routes to
App --> Profile : routes to
App --> Dashboard : routes to
App --> SoundDetail : routes to
App --> Upload : routes to
App --> LoginForm : routes to
App --> RegistrationForm : routes to

SoundBar --> Sound : controls playback
SoundDetail --> Sound : displays
Dashboard --> Sound : displays
Profile --> Sound : displays

NavBar --> App : navigation control
NavBar --> ReduxActions : dispatches search

LoginForm --> ReduxActions : dispatches auth
RegistrationForm --> ReduxActions : dispatches auth
Upload --> ReduxActions : dispatches upload
Profile --> ReduxActions : dispatches follow

ReduxActions --> Backend : API calls
Backend --> Database : queries
Backend --> Cloudinary : media storage

ReduxReducers --> ReduxStore : updates state
ReduxStore --> App : provides state
ReduxStore --> SoundBar : provides audio state
ReduxStore --> Profile : provides user data

@enduml
```

Key features of this diagram:
1. Clear separation between frontend and backend components
2. Explicit Redux architecture showing actions, reducers, and store
3. Focus on control flow with directional arrows showing component interactions
4. Main routing relationships from App component
5. State management flow through Redux
6. Backend service integrations